.SH NAME
.P
pnut.\&toml - pnut sandbox configuration file
.P
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
The \fBpnut\fR sandbox is configured entirely through a TOML file passed via
\fBpnut --config\fR.\& This page documents every section and field.\&
.P
Fields marked with a default value are optional.\& Fields marked \fBrequired\fR must
be present when their containing section is used.\&
.P
.SH SECTIONS
.P
.SS [sandbox]
.P
General sandbox settings.\& All fields are optional.\&
.P
\fBhostname\fR (string)
.RS 4
Hostname visible inside the sandbox.\& Requires \fBnamespaces.\&uts = true\fR or
validation fails.\& Default: inherit host hostname.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcwd\fR (string)
.RS 4
Working directory for the sandboxed process.\& Default: \fB/\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBmode\fR (string)
.RS 4
Execution mode.\&
.P
\fBonce\fR
.RS 4
(default) Fork via \fBclone3\fR; parent supervises child and propagates
exit status.\&
.P
.RE
\fBexecve\fR
.RS 4
Calling process unshares and exec'\&s directly; no supervising parent.\&
.P
.RE
.RE
\fBnew_session\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Call \fBsetsid\fR(2) to create a new session and disconnect from the
controlling terminal.\& Mitigates CVE-2017-5226.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdie_with_parent\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Set PR_SET_PDEATHSIG so the child is killed if the parent exits.\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBargv0\fR (string)
.RS 4
Override argv[0] for the command.\& Default: use the command path as
argv[0].\&
.P
.RE
\fBno_new_privs\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Set PR_SET_NO_NEW_PRIVS via \fBprctl\fR(2) before exec.\& Prevents \fBexecve\fR
from granting privileges (setuid binaries, file capabilities).\& Required
for unprivileged seccomp filter installation.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdisable_tsc\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Disable RDTSC and RDTSCP instructions via \fBprctl\fR(2) (PR_SET_TSC).\&
x86/x86_64 only; causes SIGSEGV on RDTSC.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBdumpable\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Set PR_SET_DUMPABLE.\& When \fBfalse\fR, prevents same-UID ptrace and
\fB/proc/<pid>/mem\fR access from outside the sandbox.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBforward_signals\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Forward signals received by the supervisor to the sandboxed child.\&
When \fBfalse\fR, any signal to the supervisor kills the child with SIGKILL.\&
Only applies in \fBonce\fR mode.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [namespaces]
.P
Controls which Linux namespaces are created.\& All fields are booleans.\&
.P
\fBuser\fR (bool)
.RS 4
User namespace.\& Required for unprivileged sandboxing.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBpid\fR (bool)
.RS 4
PID namespace.\& Child becomes PID 1.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBmount\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Mount namespace.\& Required for filesystem isolation via \fBpivot_root\fR(2).\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fButs\fR (bool)
.RS 4
UTS namespace.\& Required if \fBsandbox.\&hostname\fR is set.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBipc\fR (bool)
.RS 4
IPC namespace.\& Isolates System V IPC and POSIX message queues.\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBnet\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Network namespace.\& When \fBtrue\fR, the sandbox gets an isolated network stack
with only loopback.\& When \fBfalse\fR, it inherits the host network.\&
Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBcgroup\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Cgroup namespace.\& Default: \fBtrue\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBtime\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Time namespace.\& Virtualizes CLOCK_MONOTONIC and CLOCK_BOOTTIME.\& Requires
kernel >= 5.\&6.\& Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
\fBallow_nested_userns\fR (bool)
.RS 4
Allow the sandboxed process to create nested user namespaces.\& When
\fBfalse\fR, seccomp rules deny \fBclone3\fR (ENOSYS), \fBclone\fR and \fBunshare\fR
with namespace flags.\& Prevents sandbox escape via namespace reshaping.\&
Default: \fBfalse\fR.\&
.P
.RE
.SS [[mount]]
.P
An ordered array of filesystem mount operations.\& Each entry is a TOML
array-of-tables element.\& Mounts are applied in order before \fBpivot_root\fR.\&
.P
